body:
@lfzCarlosC 
_setup.yml_ is used to covered all environments (local, mac, etc). If you use docker-machine, setup will try to find the ip of the docker-machine and fill it in ansible hosts for you. But if you dont use docker-machine, the step is still executed cause setup.yml is not bind to a specific ansible env. In this case, you have this error (cause you don't have docker-machine in your dev env). Ansible will stop if any non-zero is returned, so in order to tell ansible go forward, we have to skip the "fatal" error.

Hope that I can give you a enough explanation. This error message is still very annoying, i agree with you

$ vagrant@vagrant-ubuntu-trusty-64:~/openwhisk/ansible$ curl -X GET http://localhost:5984/root_vagrant-ubuntu-trusty-64_whisks/whisk.system/samples/echo
{"error":"not_found","reason":"missing"}

